p: Increasing dietary DDGS levels up to 18% led to significant increases in cholesterol, total fat, and total unsaturated fatty acids (USFA) of egg yolk when compared with the control group ( Table 5). Hens fed dietary DDGS (0 and 18%) had the lowest egg U/S ratio. In addition, hens fed a diet supplemented with EEM had significantly ( p â‰¤ 0.01) higher yolk cholesterol than those fed un-supplemented diets. No significant differences were detected as a response to the combination of DDGS and EEM.
